    <li><strong>OECD</strong> — <em>OECD Survey on Drivers of Trust in Public Institutions 2024 Results</em><br>
    <a href="https://www.oecd.org/en/publications/oecd-survey-on-drivers-of-trust-in-public-institutions-2024-results_9a20554b-en.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.oecd.org/en/publications/oecd-survey-on-drivers-of-trust-in-public-institutions-2024-results_9a20554b-en.html</a></li>

    <li><strong>World Economic Forum</strong> — <em>Global Risks Report 2025</em><br>
    <a href="https://www.weforum.org/publications/global-risks-report-2025/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.weforum.org/publications/global-risks-report-2025/</a></li>

    <li><strong>World Economic Forum</strong> — <em>Global Risks Report 2026</em><br>
    <a href="https://www.weforum.org/publications/global-risks-report-2026/digest/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.weforum.org/publications/global-risks-report-2026/digest/</a></li>

    <li><strong>European Parliament Research Service</strong> — <em>Understanding Political Polarisation</em> (2025)<br>
    <a href="https://www.europarl.europa.eu/cmsdata/299492/Understanding-political-polarisation.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.europarl.europa.eu/cmsdata/299492/Understanding-political-polarisation.pdf</a></li>

    <li><strong>European Commission</strong> — <em>A Strengthened EU Code of Practice on Disinformation</em><br>
    <a href="https://commission.europa.eu/topics/countering-information-manipulation/strengthened-eu-code-practice-disinformation_en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://commission.europa.eu/topics/countering-information-manipulation/strengthened-eu-code-practice-disinformation_en</a></li>

    <li><strong>Pew Research Center</strong> — <em>Most Americans say Republican and Democratic voters cannot agree on basic facts</em> (2024)<br>
    <a href="https://www.pewresearch.org/topic/politics-policy/political-parties-polarization/political-polarization/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.pewresearch.org/topic/politics-policy/political-parties-polarization/political-polarization/</a></li>

    <li><strong>Nature Human Behaviour</strong> — <em>A systematic review of worldwide causal and correlational evidence on digital media and democracy</em><br>
    <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41562-022-01460-1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.nature.com/articles/s41562-022-01460-1</a></li>
  </ul>
</div>

